{"id":1694326,"retrievedAt":"2026-05-14T12:45:22.466Z","response":{"adult":false,"backdrop_path":null,"belongs_to_collection":null,"budget":0,"genres":[{"id":99,"name":"Documentary"}],"homepage":"","id":1694326,"imdb_id":"tt1615465","origin_country":["FR"],"original_language":"fr","original_title":"Les Dragons n'existent pas","overview":"\"Les dragons n’existent pas is a call to the dead in a stricken land, the Ardennes. The dead are not those of the last war, but the factories that have closed down one after the other: Cellatex, the Thomé-Génot foundries, Sopal Gascogne. All fallen foul of the game of musical chairs played by international financial capitalism.  Stories of strikes, machine-tool auctions, angry words, lists of grievances and industrial ruins punctuate this funeral oration, where the worker, the source of all of capitalism’s value-added, refuses to be buried in the obscurity of the Ardennes forest, the fate that befell the Roman sanctuaries in the Medieval forest.\"  (Yann Lardeau)","popularity":0.0071,"poster_path":null,"production_companies":[{"id":81540,"logo_path":null,"name":"Black Bird Productions","origin_country":"FR"}],"production_countries":[{"iso_3166_1":"FR","name":"France"}],"release_date":"2010-03-17","revenue":0,"runtime":45,"softcore":false,"spoken_languages":[{"english_name":"French","iso_639_1":"fr","name":"Français"}],"status":"Released","tagline":"","title":"Les Dragons n'existent pas","video":false,"vote_average":0,"vote_count":0,"alternative_titles":{"titles":[]},"credits":{"cast":[],"crew":[{"adult":false,"gender":0,"id":1703909,"known_for_department":"Production","name":"Guillaume Massart","original_name":"Guillaume Massart","popularity":0.0362,"profile_path":"/9JN2s08pOkFIRegMJH0atw4SSqE.jpg","credit_id":"6a04edc181c6dec7a16d6e2e","department":"Directing","job":"Director"},{"adult":false,"gender":0,"id":5112661,"known_for_department":"Directing","name":"Adrien Mitterrand","original_name":"Adrien Mitterrand","popularity":0,"pr